<h4> Job Summary</h4>



<p>QC Manager will be responsible for performing Aerospace precision inspection verifications on mechanical parts, components, assemblies, and materials using variable or attribute measuring instruments and techniques to ensure conformance with the companyâs standards. &nbsp;May include but is not limited to first article parts, in-process and final inspection on assemblies, and materials for workmanship and conformance to specifications/drawings.</p>



<h4> Essential Duties and Responsibilities:</h4>



<p><em>The primary duties and responsibilities of the Quality Control Manager consist of but are not limited to:</em></p>



<ul><li>Perform Receiving Inspection, In-Process Inspection of parts being manufactured or assembled, First Article Inspection of newly designed or revised products to meet and conform with customersâ specifications</li><li>Conferring with vendors and/or customers regarding inspection results and inspection data, and compares findings with specifications to ensure conformance to standards</li><li>Review, release and monitor work orders/job travelers to ensure the inspectorâs ability to verify requirements to meet the drawings/specifications and to check for conflicting or missing requirements on the documents</li><li>Assures product quality through maintenance of a quality system in accordance with the quality regulations and customer requirements</li><li>Ensuring all non-conformance product is correctly identified and isolated until disposition (rework or scrap) can be determined</li><li>Performing a quick visual inspection, testing, measuring, analyzing products and recording pass/fail grade of products for management review</li><li>Regular, consistent and punctual attendance is required; must be able to work overtime and weekend if necessary</li></ul>



<h4>Desired Skills and Experience:</h4>



<ul><li>MUST have experience in Aerospace CNC
manufacturing environment, AS9100 and First Article Inspection</li><li>CMM and Portable Arm experience is preferred,
with sufficient PC-DMIS and Verisurf skills</li><li>Blueprint reading, engineering drawings and
process specifications interpretation skills are strongly preferred</li><li>Ability to use precision measuring instruments
and calibrations</li><li>Working knowledge of Quality Assurance,
metrology principles and well-versed in NADCAP, ISO and AS9100</li><li>Knowledge of the materials, products, and the
commodity assigned areas of specialization</li><li>Working knowledge utilizing ERP system,
preferably JobBOSS and usage of Microsoft Office Suite</li></ul>



<p>Experience Required:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 5+ Years</p>



<p>Career Level Required:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Experienced Manager</p>



<p>Job Time/Status:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Employee / Full-Time</p>

